POSITIVELY ELIMINATED (do not re-propose): dynamic-VB ring buffer lifetime/contention (SEVEN designs failed incl. a 16MB never-wrapping ring AND today removing the skin ring entirely — both still spike); CPU skin output (engine probe over 600 draws: zero collapse, zero out-of-range bone index); index over-reference (overRead=0, maxIdx==vtxCount-1 all LODs); the skeletal batch renderer (never executes); per-frame CPU/GPU race (full present() serialization no-op). The VS is a plain uniform WVP (POSITION/NORMAL/TEXCOORD, no blend weights). char-select soft-skin bodies render CLEAN (same VS/layout/skinData) — bug is in-world only.

