For a non-multi-stream SBSSP primitive, the engine still wraps the one dynamic VB in a `VertexBufferVector`; the D3D11 side therefore reaches the vector IA bind path, not the single-VB bind path. That matters because the vector path already multiplies the dynamic slice vertex offset by stride before `IASetVertexBuffers`.
