   The draw/fetch region is not clipped by `numberOfVertices` in D3D11: `drawPartialIndexedTriangleList` takes `minimumVertexIndex` and `numberOfVertices`, but the actual call at [Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:3451](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:3451) uses only `primitiveCount`, `startIndex`, and `baseIndex`. Therefore fetches are determined by the index values in the selected index-buffer range plus `BaseVertexLocation=0`.

Verdict: for the normal single-stream SBSSP path, WRITE count == copy count == locked count (`m_vertexCount`); D3D11 can fetch outside that written range only if the index buffer range selected by `startIndex/primitiveCount` contains an index `>= m_vertexCount`, not from a lock/copy/IA offset count mismatch shown in this path.
